Serves 4 You’ll need: For the curry spice mix – 15ml ground coriander; 15ml ground cumin; 15ml ground turmeric; 5ml ground ginger; 5ml dry mustard; 5ml ground cinnamon; 1ml cayenne pepper; salt and freshly cracked black pepper For the curry – 1 x 400g can coconut milk; 1 red pepper, chopped; 1 yellow pepper, chopped; 1 x 432g can Rhodes Quality Pineapple Pieces in Syrup, drained; 4 chicken breast fillets, diced; 65ml fresh coriander leaves, chopped To serve – roti and/ or basmati rice

How to: Serve the curry over rice and garnish with the coriander. *Recipe and image by rhodesquality.com